  "prompt": "What is the heavy feeling near the larynx which one feels when he or she is feeling guilty, sad or depressed?",
  "response": "The heavy feeling near the larynx when experiencing emotions like guilt, sadness, or depression is commonly referred to as a \"lump in the throat\" sensation. This sensation is often linked to emotional stress and is thought to be a physical manifestation of such feelings. The exact cause of this sensation can be complex, involving both psychological and physiological factors.\n\nWhen you feel strong emotions, your body's autonomic nervous system may react by tightening the muscles around the throat, causing the sensation of a lump. This response can be associated with the body's fight-or-flight reaction, where stress hormones are released, leading to various physical symptoms. \n\nAdditionally, the feeling can also be related to the way the brain processes emotions, signaling to the body to prepare for possible crying or other emotional expressions, thus causing this physical sensation. If you find this sensation frequent or distressful, it's advisable to consult a healthcare professional for further evaluation and support.",
